some moments of healing 💕🌈 far from perfect but i ty for being by my side 💕

The past few months have felt like a never ending rollercoaster of emotions that i’ve had to allow myself to feel and go through. I’m not going to sugarcoat it and say what i’ve been going through has been easy, it has been nothing but devastating and traumatic. A series of events that has changed my life completely, that I hope to share with you guys when i’m ready as I know so many can relate and not feel alone too 🤍

The process has felt so slow and painful yet somehow managed to have gone by so quickly. I haven’t felt or been my best self, truly some of my worst, and it’s really hard for me to admit that. My support system of family, friends and partner have helped me so much through this dark time in my life, and I feel beyond appreciative and forever grateful. 

To everyone who reached out i’m incredibly thankful, im still getting back to so many messages. I feel so much love from all angles. Im currently working on healing my heart and soul from here on in. Thank you to everyone for being patient with me while sending so much love and light ❤️ You never know what someone is going through, always reach out and lend an open ear and let the people you love and care and let them know you’re there. The holidays are hard. Life is hard. we’re all trying our best, and it truly is okay to not be ok. I know this will all make sense one day, but what i do know now is that this has made so much room for personal growth , resilience , room to be a stronger women with so much light at the end of the tunnel 🌈✨ Thank you for following me on this crazy journey called life xx

A letter to Baby Racq✨Through my journey of self healing im learning so much about how impulsive reactions, uncontrollable emotions, toxic behaviors and patterns have affected not only my relationship with others but more importantly myself. Some of my life experiences have made me feel as though I am not worthy of love due to my past traumas. I am learning to set healthy boundaries, practice forgiveness, build trust and acceptance. Working on trying to actually breath for once in my life. Focusing more on living in the present moment all by healing my inner child, learning to be kind by reconnecting, loving and accepting her. Being carefree, laughing, living and just being HAPPY🤍 Thank you @wecarespaca for being a huge impact along my path. I am trusting that I am right exactly where I need to be 🤍

Floating up in the clouds in pure tranquility reminiscing on how our 10 day experience @wecarespaca has truly been transformative and extremely life changing. We challenged our bodies, minds and souls to a place we never thought it could go. walking in to a community of open minded / likeminded individuals where everyone was their true, honest most vulnerable and open hearted selves. I’ve never experienced a place so special. A path to wellness, healing and happiness im making a promise to myself from here on in ✨

It was filled with manifestation workshops, coaching, healing ceremonies, yoga and meditation and reflection. Currently trying to create a balance in my life to face and work on myself so that all areas in my life can continue flourish and elevate @laina_caltagirone you are such a positive source of light in life and truly amazing at what you do✨Thank you for bringing likeminded souls together. I cried, laughed and created meaningful conversations that made me feel less alone ✨healing is an upwards spiral but so excited to be on this very challenging yet extremely rewarding journey as I’m finally starting to feel all the abundance and light in life has to offer 🤍✨🌴🇲🇽
